author: Danny Davis
title: An eighth victory over Westlake would put Lake Travis in elite group
text:
An eighth victory over Westlake would put Lake Travis in elite group 3:31 p.m. Wednesday, Oct. 21, 2015 | Filed in: High School Comments 0 ﻿ 
Westlake and Lake Travis meet for the 10th time on Friday, with the Cavaliers boasting a 7-2 record against the Chaparrals. Last year’s 24-7 victory was Lake Travis’ seventh straight over Westlake, which last beat the Cavaliers when it recorded a 28-21 win in 2007. 
Lake Travis is the only school to defeat Westlake more than four consecutive times, but the Cavaliers are not the team that has handed Westlake its most losses. Since it played its first varsity football game in 1969, Westlake has suffered eight losses to both Round Rock and Georgetown.
